# Presentation Speaker Notes Quality

Applies to all speaker-note edits in this presentation repository.

## Notes style and delivery
- Write notes for spoken delivery, not for documentation reading.
- Keep sentences natural and rhythmic, with clear transitions to the next idea.
- Expand the meaning of slide bullets instead of repeating them verbatim.
- Include lightweight pacing cues when useful (for example: pause, emphasize, transition).
- Keep language confident and practical; avoid filler and overlong paragraphs.

## Tool mention reliability (very strict)
- Any tool feature mentioned in notes must be verified before being stated as fact.
- Acceptable verification sources:
  - official vendor documentation,
  - repository/project docs,
  - explicit material provided in the current context.
- If verification is missing, explicitly mark as unknown and avoid feature promises.
- Preferred safe phrasing:
  - "Verified capability: ..."
  - "Unknown/unverified in current context: ..."
- Never fabricate integrations, automations, or platform support claims.

## Alignment checks
- Ensure each note block supports the slide's title and bullets.
- Preserve continuity across slides by ending with a forward transition when appropriate.
